{"name":"Shady Affairs","pages":[{"sort":200000,"name":"Cover","type":"image","_id":"HND7U8h5ZtBFhDln","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"image":{"caption":"Tiziano Crescia depicts the fair of Atiatium in Arcotia, where a festive atmosphere is the setting for mysterious and dangerous intrigues"},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":"modules/wagham-quickstart/Artwork/Shady_Affairs_Shady-2.jpg","system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":300000,"name":"Credits","type":"text","_id":"EAqBvk8b83TTpk9d","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"modules/wagham-quickstart/Artwork/Blu%20e%20texture.png\" style=\"border:none\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /><p><strong>Publisher</strong>: Wagham</p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Project Lead</strong>: Paolo Ferrante</p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Map Designers</strong>: Pierpaolo Pellegrino; Lanfranco Milillo</p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Editor</strong>: Paolo Ferrante</p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Artist</strong>: Tiziano Crescia</p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Foundry VTT Converter</strong>: Lorenzo de Virgilio (Calcifer)</p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><a href=\"https://wagham.it/\">www.Wagham.it</a></p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><br /></strong><a href=\"https://www.patreon.com/Wagham\"><strong>Patreon</strong></a><strong>     </strong><a href=\"https://discord.gg/Rgd6cnbupH\"><strong>Discord</strong></a><strong>     </strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/IlRegnodiWagham/\"><strong>Facebook</strong></a></p><p><em>Wagham: Shady Affairs is a Dungeons and Dragons 5th Edition compatible adventure designed as a supplement for game masters to use in their adventures or campaigns. This product is compliant with the Open Game License (OGL) located on the last page of this product.</em></p><p></p><p><em><strong>Product Identity:</strong> The following items are hereby identified as Product Identity, as defined in the Open Game License version 1.0a, Section 1(e), and are not Open Content: All trademarks, registered trademarks, proper names (characters, deities, etc.), dialogue, plots, storylines, locations, characters, artwork, and trade dress. (Elements that have previously been designated as Open Game Content or are in the public domain are not included in this declaration.)</em></p><p><em><br /><strong>Open Content:</strong> Except for material designated as Product Identity (see above), the game mechanics of this Wagham product are Open Game Content, as defined in the Open Game License version 1.0a Section 1(d). No portion of this work other than the material designated as Open Game Content may be reproduced in any form without written permission.</em></p><p></p><p style=\"text-align:center\">Copyright © Wagham 2022</p><img src=\"modules/wagham-quickstart/Artwork/Wagham_Token_2%20(1).png\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" style=\"border:none\" /></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":400000,"name":"What's Included?","type":"text","_id":"GkdOZMo3lugU0guY","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">In this module of <em>Shady Affairs</em> you will find a preview of the supplement of rules, compatible with the 5e system, created by Wagham:</span></p><p></p><h3><strong>@UUID[.pBa3fHdoGfPpEvfx]{Feats}</strong></h3><p>Where would your hero be without Feats? Each one gives him or her a special ability that fits their character. And there are many more Feats in Wagham!</p><p></p><h3><strong>@UUID[.vx8TM7MOnNF0xBN6]{Spells}</strong></h3><p>Defend or attack, there is one for everyone! Spells represent the means by which magical effects can be realized. They are the primary tool of spellcasters!</p><p></p><h3><strong>@UUID[.a4ThNjzxexdedcII]{Missions Generator}</strong></h3><p>Our Missions generators will provide your adventurers with enough excitement and danger to last a lifetime. We have carefully crafted this set of modular quests to never run out of missions, so no boredom shall befall our heroes.</p><p></p><h3><strong>@UUID[.sviUdB0XXDrEls5T]{Subclasses}</strong></h3><p>Featuring a variety of subclasses each with its own unique set of skills and attributes, there's something for everyone in the family.</p><p></p><section style=\"background-color:powderblue;padding:10px\"><p><em><strong>In the Empire of Arcotia…</strong></em></p><p>our brave adventurers will reach the city of Atiatum in their way to Vinoverno, there they will be forced to reconsider their plans as the main route is blocked. Our heroes will find themselves in the middle of a situation, they will meet different characters, to whom will they swear their loyalty? To whom will they pledge their allegiance?</p></section></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":600000,"name":"Subclasses","type":"text","_id":"sviUdB0XXDrEls5T","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><em>Featuring a variety of subclasses each with its own unique set of skills and attributes, there's something for everyone in the family.</em></span></p><p></p><p>@UUID[.eiU5eGIeTi9LcAWV]{Cleric: Beauty Domain}</p><p>@UUID[.4xn1bHqV7jhTlMGX]{Barbarian:Path of the Magic Denier}</p><p>@UUID[.cnvhpvA0Nq3FXhaY]{Wizard: Archivist}</p><img src=\"modules/wagham-quickstart/Artwork/13_-_Impero_di_Arcotia-1.jpeg\" />","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":500000,"name":"Feats","type":"text","_id":"pBa3fHdoGfPpEvfx","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>A feat represents a talent or area of experience that gives the character certain special abilities. It can include training, experience, and abilities beyond what a class gives.</em></p><h3><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.feats.h90y4aPOV1921Gz5]{Self-Destructive Magic}</strong></h3><p><em>Prerequisite: half elementals</em></p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Your race was born from the war experiments of humans: they infused heavy doses of elemental magic to create living weapons. Early specimens were highly unstable, with strong powers but ended up dying in excruciating torment. You, like your ancestors, put your own physical integrity at risk to channel your magical power.</span></p><p>You gain the following benefits:</p><p>• Your CON score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p><p>• As a bonus action, you can consume a number of hit dice to gain a spell slot of a level equal to the number of hit dice spent, up to a maximum equal to your proficiency bonus. You also roll the corresponding hit dice and reduce your maximum HP by the result you get. For example, if you are a 5th-level fighter, you can consume up to 3 life dice at a time and recover up to a 3rd-level spell slot, after which you roll 1d10 for the level of the recovered spell slot and reduce your maximum HP by the total gained. This reduction in maximum HP cannot be reduced or cancelled by any source and lasts until you complete a long rest.</p><p></p><h3><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.feats.FZi7Tw0Z0mB03DQE]{Mighty Arms}</strong></h3><p><em>Prerequisite: trait \"Powerful Build\"; STR 13 or higher</em></p><p>You are dedicated to improving your physique, being able to lift and throw opponents with ease.</p><p>You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>Your STR score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p></li><li><p>You gain proficiency in STR (Athletics), or expertise if you already possessed proficiency.</p></li><li><p>As an attack action, you can throw a target that is grabbed by you. You cannot cast creatures that are two size categories or larger than you. If you are able to make multiple attacks through the attack action, this replaces one of them. You make a STR (Athletic) check against a STR (Athletic) check of the target. The target is no longer grabbed by you (regardless of the result). If successful, you throw the target into a space within 6 m (20 ft.) of you and the target falls prone suffering 1d6 + your STR mod. bludgeoning damage. If the space is occupied by a creature, it must make a DEX save with DC equal to 8 + your competence bonus + your STR mod.. If it fails, it takes damage like the target and falls prone. The primary target, in this case, lands in a space of your choice within 5 ft (1.5 m) of the secondary target and suffers the normal effects of the throw.</p></li></ul><p></p><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.feats.pJ3Q5cvy0ZW2121c]{Night's Emissary}</h3><p><em>Prerequisite: vampires</em></p><p>Darkness is the domain of vampires and their spawn. You have neared vampire skills, becoming an experienced and stealthy hunter of the night. You gain the following benefits:</p><p>• Your darkvision increases by 60 ft (18 m).</p><p>• You can transform into a @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.monsters.qav2dvMIUiMQCCsy]{bat}, a @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.monsters.yawTeS8u2FCfzzZH]{wolf}, or a @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.monsters.pozQUPTnLZW8epox]{rat}. This ability follows the rules of the druid’s Wild Form, but it does not count in the total number of uses of this ability if you have druid levels, it lasts a maximum of 1 hour, and you do not have to meet certain levels to select one of these creatures. You can use this ability twice, and you recover the spent uses when you complete a long rest.</p><p>• You learn the Suggestion spell. You can cast it without spending spell slots once this way, and you cannot cast it again until you complete a long rest. You can also cast it using spell slots of an appropriate level. INT, WIS or CHA is your spellcasting characteristic for this spell when you cast it with this ability (you determine this when you choose this talent).</p><img src=\"modules/wagham-quickstart/Artwork/14_-_Impero_di_Arcotia_Vinoverno-1.jpg\" alt=\"Vinoverno\" />","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OFM4iJAVuKY2LvAj.JournalEntryPage.pBa3fHdoGfPpEvfx"}}},{"sort":550000,"name":"Spells","type":"text","_id":"vx8TM7MOnNF0xBN6","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<img src=\"modules/wagham-quickstart/Artwork/spell-bottle_1.png\" style=\"width:150px;height:300px;border:none;float:right\" /><p style=\"text-align:center\"><em>Spells represent the means by which magical effects can be realized. They can have arcane, divine or even innate origins; they manifest themselves in a wide variety of forms.</em></p><p></p><h3><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.spells.99uJRknGfF9fVa6b]{Amanuenses’ Touch}</strong></h3><p><em>Transmutation Cantrip</em></p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Touch</p><p><strong>Components:</strong> V, S, M (a sheet of parchment large enough to hold all the text you want to transcribe, a quill and a ink-filled bottle that the spell consumes)</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Instantaneous</p><p><strong>Classes:</strong> Artificer, Bard, Cleric, Warlock, Wizard</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">You touch a page of written text that you want to copy, after which you touch a blank sheet of parchment and the text magically appears on the new sheet. All writing, illustrations, and other elements are reproduced in the new document in your handwriting or drawing style. This spell does not reproduce the magical properties of a piece of writing.</span></p><p></p><h3><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.spells.fEd9EOJAbgOmgGWi]{Tactical Accuracy}</strong></h3><p><em>1st-level enchantment</em></p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 reaction, which you make when a creature allied to you (other than yourself) within range rolls an attack or ability check</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 60 feet (18 m)</p><p><strong>Components:</strong> V</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Instantaneous</p><p><strong>Classes:</strong> Bard, Cleric</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">You roll a 1d4 and add the resulting number to the roll the creature just made, it will use the new result to determine its success or failure.</span></p><p></p><h3><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.spells.XPDfAMssHeGJQrZe]{Divine Protection}</strong></h3><p><em>2nd-level enchantment</em></p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 reaction, which you perform when a creature within range that you can see suffers a critical hit</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 20 ft (6 m)</p><p><strong>Components:</strong> V, S, M (a small blunt blade)</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Instantaneous</p><p><strong>Classes:</strong> Cleric, Paladin</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Your prayer partially protects the target from the attack. The critical hit counts as a normal hit for the purpose of determining the damage.</span></p><p></p><h3><strong>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.spells.RSjjdY6olr4l8Q2a]{Impassable Limit}</strong></h3><p><em>4st-level enchantment</em></p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 reaction, which you take when a creature moves within 30 ft (9 m) of you or an ally in sight</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Sight</p><p><strong>Components:</strong> V, S, M (a fragment of granite)</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Classes:</strong> Bard, Cleric, Paladin, Wizard</p><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">When a creature you can see moves within 30 ft. (9 m) of you or an ally, you utter a command to force it to stop. The target must make a WIS save. If it fails, its speed drops to 0 until the start of your next turn. The spell has no effect if the target is undead, if it does not understand your language, or if the latter’s command causes it to end its movement on obviously dangerous terrain, such as a fire or a pit.</span></p><p></p><img src=\"modules/wagham-quickstart/Artwork/Arcotia-2.png\" style=\"border:none\" alt=\"Arcotia's countryside\" />","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OFM4iJAVuKY2LvAj.JournalEntryPage.vx8TM7MOnNF0xBN6"}}},{"sort":787500,"name":"Missions Generator","type":"text","_id":"a4ThNjzxexdedcII","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>Pimpus Magnus</h1><p>Criminal and pleasure slave trader</p><h2>Complex Missions</h2><table style=\"text-align:left;width:80%\"><caption style=\"text-align:left;font-size:120%\">@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.rolltables.zOWEDa19OKzla91c]{Pimpus Magnus - Complex Missions}</caption><thead style=\"background-color:#2754b3\"><tr><th style=\"width:11%;text-align:left\">d4</th><th style=\"text-align:left\">Complex Missions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.NDE7pkw3kCrtatDm]{Selling the three best slaves to Laidus}</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.kH72Ei6e6Q0HvXrx]{Abducting an aasimar from the High Star Temple}</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.6fKw95dLxysPdBPs]{Destroying the goods of Numa Fellatium}</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.BfnmmLqenIjDx5JY]{Breaking up the rival gang of Inconsiderata}</td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Simple Missions</h2><table style=\"text-align:left;width:80%\"><caption style=\"text-align:left;font-size:120%\">@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.rolltables.dR9cxwQLlzuKyRcH]{Pimpus Magnus - Simple Missions}</caption><thead style=\"background-color: