Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.uSZ5xxb0Sf0fZLei]{Stopping Pederastichus harassment}</td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Simple Missions</h2><table style=\"text-align:left;width:80%\"><caption style=\"text-align:left;font-size:120%\">@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.rolltables.dR9cxwQLlzuKyRcH]{Exaggera - Simple Missions}</caption><thead style=\"background-color:#2754b3\"><tr><th style=\"width:11%;text-align:left\">d8</th><th>Simple Missions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.ha6Lq1ForrGCaBHU]{Convert Inconsiderata}</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.WBVOV4PGhb3qjVD9]{Finding the money stolen by pickpockets}</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.CzQUrJ8vbXGc9aQv]{Uncovering the conspiracy}</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.1dCs1zi7hCmqMCbu]{Escorting the clerics of beauty to the fountain}</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.4Dd5wW2FItzKGsvN]{Redeeming pawns from Pecunio}</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.LWQIfZ4cHxG9lkVN]{Convincing passers-by to donate to the temple}</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.AZ9ReleEdNYg294w]{Recruiting a new heroine}</td></tr><tr><td>8</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.SJ0HPracLh2lOtpS]{Training the clerics}</td></tr></tbody></table><h1>Numa Fellatium</h1><p>The merchant determined to be on everyone’s lips.</p><h2>Complex Missions</h2><table style=\"text-align:left;width:80%\"><caption style=\"text-align:left;font-size:120%\">@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.rolltables.I4ImcM7Do7Xa1SJo]{Numa Fellatium - Complex Missions}</caption><thead style=\"background-color:#2754b3\"><tr><th style=\"width:11%;text-align:left\">d4</th><th>Complex Missions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.mWUcQ0TiI4EOBvWE]{Dressing and escorting the model}</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.JyH4vRQ7bfXt2ceo]{Stopping Pecunio's extortions}</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.4SlUqYvbMYrUkPE8]{Preventing Inconsiderata's cheating}</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.s8UhzDCNAyK8jscX]{Stealing the chest of Laidus}</td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Simple Missions</h2><table style=\"text-align:left;width:80%\"><caption style=\"text-align:left;font-size:120%\">@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.rolltables.1d2yzjXHlAlk1WdS]{Numa Fellatium - Simple Missions}</caption><thead style=\"background-color:#2754b3\"><tr><th style=\"width:11%;text-align:left\">d8</th><th>Simple Missions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.JOunoVLyVrtDdIrx]{Dressing the clerics of beauty}</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.MrqlmhxRRwJkWhmr]{Winning the favour of Præpuce Scæmola}</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.ZiCHT3vLLwcVJ53M]{Dressing Inconsiderata}</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.rvv4mstMozBrebBu]{Hiring halflings slaves}</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.gzZkHWrsDdldYxso]{Securing supplies from the winners}</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.UXPf9fuicRYYSV8L]{Finding new inspirations and trends}</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.3obpBMKJU6K1KTJJ]{Dressing the young clerics}</td></tr><tr><td>8</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.xpCJvOpoY6OXDQxi]{Denouncing Pimpus Magnus}</td></tr></tbody></table><h1>Pecunio</h1><p>The greedy merchant</p><h2>Complex Missions</h2><table style=\"text-align:left;width:80%\"><caption style=\"text-align:left;font-size:120%\">@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.rolltables.W2ohOIIqSoKEt72L]{Pecunio - Complex Missions}</caption><thead style=\"background-color:#2754b3\"><tr><th style=\"width:11%;text-align:left\">d4</th><th>Complex Missions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.3cE9FwBMzxsjyVmm]{Real Estate}</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.wT40QUFKgjOCn9W5]{Sale of indulgences}</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.UgkRjGmO2MU6L5bk]{Insuring both beauties}</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.qEvxwAgYnnCtzm5q]{Beating the competition}</td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Simple Missions</h2><table style=\"text-align:left;width:80%\"><caption style=\"text-align:left;font-size:120%\">@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.rolltables.TLOoXfTj7iwwGESn]{Pecunio - Simple Missions}</caption><thead style=\"background-color:#2754b3\"><tr><th style=\"width:11%;text-align:left\">d8</th><th>Simple Missions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.sHPDrIOBClYOv04R]{Debt collection}</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.aJF7IPJjen0Kz2m1]{Blackmailing clerics}</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.mIq0m8FsPqEJG9M6]{Præpuce Scæmola’s life insurance}</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.7lNkbBNhKNDpVplk]{Begging for money by cripples}</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.M8cwlXsrm7u5Jvuy]{Winning the fruit fair with a fake banana}</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.twWXmAh8pYzhxKz1]{Getting the best matches...}</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.5OQfflkpug2yd2ZQ]{Two birds with one stone}</td></tr><tr><td>8</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.lPuuKNwtTG8njhdt]{Trafficking Caliphate's migrants}</td></tr></tbody></table><h1>Don Pérignon</h1><p>The Cleric of Intrigue</p><h2>Complex Missions</h2><table style=\"text-align:left;width:80%\"><caption style=\"text-align:left;font-size:120%\">@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.rolltables.LfFfypZcifLroxy2]{Don Pérignon - Complex Missions}</caption><thead style=\"background-color:#2754b3\"><tr><th style=\"width:11%;text-align:left\">d4</th><th>Complex Missions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.MGByzFR13yPm3izc]{Assassinate and replace guards}</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.bZLQYuSQmI4DhAjC]{Bribing the guards}</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.XFJ1v1hgqYgEGWRF]{An exotic beauty}</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.UPug2UulBkMmerLx]{A refined thirst}</td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Simple Missions</h2><table style=\"text-align:left;width:80%\"><caption style=\"text-align:left;font-size:120%\">@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.rolltables.Z2kostm6TkiRNUnV]{Don Pérignon - Simple Missions}</caption><thead style=\"background-color:#2754b3\"><tr><th style=\"width:11%;text-align:left\">d8</th><th>Simple Missions</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.e9N65OZVWdJqmTpb]{Allying with Laidus}</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.gQTpreprJA5ZlmWq]{Infiltrating spies from the Caliphate}</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.hfLHxsNpTMmwSRx7]{Copying documents}</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.IzMsYoyO5Ss8w9Zk]{Discovering Pecunio's aims}</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.sueArQlZDwMR9NIT]{Infiltrating altar boys}</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.HYHqcny4AwRaNvSS]{Getting folks to talk}</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.InO902Iaqf07GVE7]{A pizza with friends}</td></tr><tr><td>8</td><td>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.MExIzroymFHd9P1O]{Hiding traces}</td></tr></tbody></table>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.wagham-quickstart.journalentry.OFM4iJAVuKY2LvAj.JournalEntryPage.a4ThNjzxexdedcII"}}},{"sort":650000,"name":"Wizard: Archivist","type":"text","_id":"cnvhpvA0Nq3FXhaY","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses.UwOtI9u6O4IQyQE4]{Archivist}</p><p><em><strong>Restriction: Only Elves from Ornwelun island</strong></em></p><p><em>Only elves from the Ornwelun island can choose this wizard subclass; however, your DM can remove this restriction if you are playing another setting or for any other reason.</em></p><p><em>After a lifetime of isolation, devoted to study in the dusty libraries of Ornwelun, the most knowledgeable wizards are awarded the rank of archivist. These elderly scholars, find their power in the infinite theoretical knowledge of the arcane arts and possess grimoires filled with spells to suit every need.</em></p><h3><em>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.opukIwmwzYEfVcHX]{Arcane Erudite}</em></h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Starting at 2nd level, the time and money you spend copying a spell into your spellbook is halved.</span></p></div><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.dkBE0tGoOA537MEW]{Academic}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p>At 2nd level, you learn to speak, read and write two languages of your choice. In addition, you gain one of the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>You gain proficiency in two of the following abilities (your choice):@skill[arcana], @skill[nature], @skill[religion], or @skill[history].</p></li><li><p>Choose one of your proficiency in Intelligence-based abilities (except Investigation). Your proficiency bonus doubles for each skill check made using your chosen skill.</p></li></ul><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.96dvgSfANPinZLUb]{Meticulous Preparation}</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Starting at 6th level, when you complete a long rest, you can prepare an extra number of spells equal to your proficiency bonus. The spells must be of a level with which you have spell slots.</span></p><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.BeCms9dGoRwiV2ye]{Mental Archives}</h3><p>Starting at 10th level, if you spend 10 minutes studying your spellbook, you can replace a number of wizard spells - equal to your proficiency bonus - that you have prepared, with different spells - of a level in which you have spell slots - in your book. You can use this privilege once, and you cannot do so until you complete a long rest.</p><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.Mhzudj4sDV8nhAi3]{Eclectic Research}</h3><p>At 14th level, you can learn magic of any kind and form. Choose, and add to your spellbook, two spells of any class that belong to a level at which you are able to cast spells, as indicated in the class table, or a cantrip. The spells you choose count as wizard spells exclusively for you and cannot be transcribed by other wizards.</p><p></p></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OFM4iJAVuKY2LvAj.JournalEntryPage.cnvhpvA0Nq3FXhaY"}}},{"sort":625000,"name":"Cleric: Beauty Domain","type":"text","_id":"eiU5eGIeTi9LcAWV","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<img src=\"modules/wagham-quickstart/Artwork/Stella_Cometa_-_05.png\" style=\"width:200px;height:300px;border:none;float:right\" /><p>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses.Unc5SOI4pXVBHEQ7]{Beauty Domain}</p><p><em><strong>Restriction: Only Humans and Aasimar of the Empire of Arcotia</strong></em></p><p><em>Only Humans and Aasimar of the Empire of Arcotia may choose this cleric subclass; however, your DM may remove this restriction if you are playing in another setting or for any other reason.</em></p><p><em>Some clerics of Vinoverno are so devoted to the High Star that their faith aims at nothing more than worshipping her, imitating her in everything and basking in her celestial perfection. Most of these clerics are maidens who hope, by imitating the High Star, to one day be chosen to serve in such a role; but there is also no shortage of young men who undertake this faith out of pure adoration of the High Star and imitate her because they see her as an ideal of perfection. What most strikes young people inexperienced in theology is precisely the celestial goodness and beauty of this divinity. These clerics - while sharing all other aspects of worship - focus on these points in particular and the High Star rewards their devotion by granting them its divine favour. A large part of the day is devoted to one's beauty routine, to choosing the most suitable attire for the occasion that best showcases one's aesthetic gifts: being beautiful is not only good for oneself but also good for others who enjoy the sight, what is good is beautiful. It is not surprising that the undead are so ugly while the High Star is so beautiful: beauty is synonymous with goodness.</em></p><p></p><div><h2><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: iRdW\">Beauty Domain Spells</span></h2><table style=\"width:100%;height:102px\"><thead style=\"background-color:#2754b3\"><tr style=\"height:17px\"><th class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\">Cleric Level</th><th class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\" data-rd-isroller=\"false\">Spells</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">1st</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.eS7XnnApoxRxYXPs]{Charm Person}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.ge3Saet9zPTDyaoL]{Heroism}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">3rd</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.30ZgXtijJVCxQk5N]{Enthrall}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.zMAWdyc8UVb37BK4]{Suggestion}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">5th</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.BP3GCwa66IAw1yTG]{Daylight}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.6g3WLOZ2u0EbaLAd]{Hypnotic Pattern}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">7th</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.9hQXdMSmerkTsHDe]{Confusion}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.VtCXMdyM6mAdIJZb]{Death Ward}</td></tr><tr style=\"height:17px\"><td class=\"col-4 text-center\" style=\"width:30.442%;height:17px\">9th</td><td class=\"col-8 text-left\" style=\"width:69.2465%;height:17px\">@Compendium[dnd5e.spells.91Sw6vOIaO7U8DvM]{Dominate Person}, @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.Pyzmm8R7rVsNAPsd]{Mass Cure Wounds}</td></tr></tbody></table></div><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.Wkt1byueIXBouoZR]{How Beautiful She Is}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p>Starting at 1st level, you become a symbol of beauty: opponents hesitate to even brush against you. As a bonus action, you can replicate the @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.gvdA9nPuWLck4tBl]{Sanctuary} spell for one minute, but you can target only yourself. The DC is your spellcasting DC. You do not lose this bene-</p><p>fit if you cast spells that charm hostile creatures, as long as you do not deal damage. As long as this privilege is active, you give off bright light within a radius of 20 ft (6 m) and dim light for an additional 20 ft (6 m). You can use this privilege a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all spent uses when you end a long rest.</p></div><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.8eSMcKkWV2pCKL9T]{How Good She Is}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p>At 1st level, you gain proficiency in the abilities @skill[persuasion] and @skill[performance].</p></div><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.lgnBBdlqt3ie4mPL]{Channel Divinity: Blinding Beauty}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p>Starting at 2nd level, you can use Channeling Divinity to invoke the beauty of the High Star.</p><p>As an action, you present your Holy Symbol and emit a sphere of holy light that dazzles enemies. Any hostile creature within 20 ft (6 m) must make a CON save against your spellcasting DC. If it fails, it is blinded for 1 minute. A creature may repeat the save at the end of its turn. If it passes, the effect on itself ends.</p></div><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.Z4TLGFbw7cXovzeT]{How Generous She Is}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p>Starting at 6th level, your beauty refreshes spirits in times of need.</p><p>As a reaction, when you or an allied creature within 30 ft (9 m) of you, that you can see, fails a save on INT, WIS,or CHA or a CHA-based ability check, you can allow the roll to be repeated, adding your WIS mod. to the result. You may use this privilege after you see the result but before the DM states whether the roll was successful or not. You can use this privilege a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain the spent uses when you complete a long rest.</p></div><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.1HD8G4WGHiuPBdra]{Enhanced Cantrip}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p>Starting at 8th level, you add your WIS mod to the damage you deal with any cleric cantrip.</p></div><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.8UYJICxUFG3jAbgu]{Astonishing Beauty}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p>Starting from the 17th level, as an action, you can decide to unleash the pure light of the High Star. You emit bright light within a radius of 150 ft (45 m) and dim light for an additional 150 ft (45 m). The light lasts for one minute or until you use an action to interrupt it. When you cast a spell and target only allied creatures you can ignore the range of the spell and choose targets from creatures within this light.</p></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OFM4iJAVuKY2LvAj.JournalEntryPage.eiU5eGIeTi9LcAWV"}}},{"sort":637500,"name":"Barbarian:Path of the Magic Denier","type":"text","_id":"4xn1bHqV7jhTlMGX","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses.Lbe63dSh0aEN1TAC]{Path of the Magic Denier}</p><div><p><em><strong>Restriction: Only Dragonborn from Fo'Khar island</strong></em></p><p><em>Only dragonborn from the Fo’Khar island can choose this barbarian subclass; however, your DM can remove this restriction if you are playing another setting or for any other reason.</em></p><p><em>Shur’Khan is the only god. Only Shur’Khan’s powers are real. Magic is weakness, magic is fiction. Among the dragonborn tribes of Fo’Khar Island it is common not to believe in magic that is not derived from the dragon god Shur’Khan.</em></p><p><em>A small circle of Fo’Khar barbarians is so firmly convinced of this conception that they repudiate magic to such an extent that it is weak against them and in some cases, even vain. Just as a druid does not wear metal on his skin because it is believed to be against the spirits, so the magic denier does not accept magic: he always rejects all forms of spells as an impure and unholy imitation of Shur’Khan.</em></p></div><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.w9ek0H3cOgUQcSql]{Magic Denial}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Starting at 3rd level, veneration toward the dragon god turns you away from magic, whether defensive or offensive. The number of magic items you can attune </span>to at the same time is 2.</p><p>While you are in rage, you gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>You become resistant to damage from spells and magical effects.</p></li><li><p>You have advantage on saves against spells and magical effects.</p></li><li><p>When you receive healing from a spell, you recover only half the normal HP.</p></li><li><p>You are considered unwilling when a spell affects you.</p></li></ul><p></p></div><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.hErYuHeXKxhWQiOz]{Wrathful Outburst}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p>Starting at 3rd level, as long as you are in rage, when a creature you can see casts a spell or magic effect, you can move toward it by half your movement speed after the spell or ability takes effect. You can no longer move this way until the beginning of your next turn.</p><p></p><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.UoHrW6iQ36fp3Wkd]{Tenacity of Shur'Khan}</h3><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">Starting at 6th level, when you make a save against a spell or magical effect, you can choose to make a CON save instead of the required roll. You can use this privilege a number of times equal to your CON mod. and you regain all spent uses when you complete a long rest.</span></p></div><p></p><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.yBazwSfjCYy0O8rA]{Adversion to Magic}</h3><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\" data-source=\"iRdW\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\">At 10th level, your hatred of magic becomes so strong that you can wipe it out. As long as you are in rage, you can use the attack action to make a special attack to break a spell. If you are able to make multiple attacks through the attack action, this replaces one of them. Instead of making a roll to hit, you replicate the effects of a @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.15Fa6q1nH27XfbR8]{Dispel Magic}. The range of the effect is equal to the range of the weapon you wield. The spellcasting characteristic for this effect is CON. You can use this privilege a number of times equal to your CON mod. and you regain all spent u</span>ses when you end a long rest.</p><p>Also, when you deal damage to a creature concentrating on a spell, that creature suffers disadvantage on the save it makes to maintain concentration.</p><p></p><h3>@UUID[Compendium.wagham-quickstart.subclasses-features.W0TGOhdiMiJPPiih]{Avatar of Antimagic}</h3><p>Starting at 14th level you emanate an aura that intimidates opponents and hinders them from using magical abilities.</p><p>When a hostile creature within 10 ft (3 m) of you casts a spell or uses a magical effect, it must make a WIS save.</p><p>The DC is equal to 8 + your CON mod + your proficiency bonus. If it fails, the spell or magic effect fails and has no effect.</p></div>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OFM4iJAVuKY2LvAj.JournalEntryPage.4xn1bHqV7jhTlMGX"}}}],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OFM4iJAVuKY2LvAj"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670914813304,"modifiedTime":1671154564437,"lastModifiedBy":"kg10vII5VzQknnnc"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"kg10vII5VzQknnnc":3},"_id":"QTZ0Bf80aaIHXtNT"}
